1.11	Pasur_(game)	Pasur (card game)	Pasur is a card game of Persian origin. Played widely in Iran, it is played similarly to the Italian game of Cassino and even more similarly to the Egyptian game of Bastra. Pasur is also known by the names Chah창r Barg (4 cards), Haft Kh창j (seven clubs) or Haft Va Chah창r, Y창zdah (7+4=11, the significance being that players want to win 7 clubs in a game of 4-card hands where 11 is a winning number).	
